<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>Meta in Talks to Lease Computing Power to Anthropic in Potential $10 Billion Deal</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/technology/meta-anthropic-ai-computing-power.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/technology/meta-anthropic-ai-computing-power.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/technology/meta-anthropic-ai-computing-power.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A deal would underline how scarce computing power is for artificial intelligence development, and could create a new business for Meta.</description><dc:creator>Eli Tan and Mike Isaac</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2026 16:17:06 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Meta</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Startup</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Enterprise Computing</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/17/multimedia/17biz-meta-anthropic-qjkb/17biz-meta-anthropic-qjkb-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Dustin Chambers for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>A data center owned by Meta in Georgia. A deal with Anthropic could potentially alleviate pressure on Meta from investors, who have questioned how much it has been spending on data centers.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>The A.I. Trade Secrets War + Economists Say ‘We Must Act Now’ + HatGPT</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/podcasts/hardfork-ai-trade-secrets.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/podcasts/hardfork-ai-trade-secrets.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/podcasts/hardfork-ai-trade-secrets.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>“I don’t know if the public understands this, but these companies hate each other.”</description><dc:creator>Kevin Roose, Casey Newton, Whitney Jones, Rachel Cohn, Vjeran Pavic, Alyssa Moxley, Dan Powell, Elisheba Ittoop, Rowan Niemisto and Diane Wong</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2026 11:00:03 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">science</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Apple</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lorde</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-audio</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/17/podcasts/17hardfork-AI-Wars/17hardfork-AI-Wars-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.png" medium="image"><media:credit>Photo Illustration by The New York Times; Images: Getty Images</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>Judge Dismisses Suit Accusing Apple of Failing to Limit Child Sex Abuse Material</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/15/technology/apple-lawsuit-child-sexual-abuse-dismissed.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/15/technology/apple-lawsuit-child-sexual-abuse-dismissed.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/15/technology/apple-lawsuit-child-sexual-abuse-dismissed.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The lawsuit highlighted concerns that the privacy of Apple’s iCloud allows illegal material to be easily stored and shared on the service.</description><dc:creator>Kalley Huang</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 18:58:17 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Rape</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Child Abuse</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cloud computing</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Child pornography</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Apple</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">iCloud</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Product liability</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Noël Wise</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Decisions and Verdicts</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Privacy</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/15/multimedia/15biz-apple-csam-fkvc/15biz-apple-csam-fkvc-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Karsten Moran for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>An Apple Store in Manhattan. Regulators are starting to pay attention to concerns that iCloud’s privacy makes it easier to share child sexual abuse material.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Someone Used A.I. to Write an Unauthorized Biography of Me. I Don’t Recommend Reading It.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/16/technology/ai-slop-books-biography-amazon.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/16/technology/ai-slop-books-biography-amazon.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/16/technology/ai-slop-books-biography-amazon.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Someone used A.I. to write my biography. Thousands more of those books are polluting Amazon. Who is behind all this drivel?</description><dc:creator>Kashmir Hill</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2026 15:12:35 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Books</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Writer</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Publishing</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/16/multimedia/16biz-AI-biographies-vpmw/16biz-AI-biographies-vpmw-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Ahmed Gaber for The New York Times</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>How Meta’s Threads Became as Popular as X</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/05/technology/threads-meta-twitter-x.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/05/technology/threads-meta-twitter-x.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/05/technology/threads-meta-twitter-x.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The social platform that Meta once positioned as a rival to Elon Musk’s X now has 500 million monthly users. It increasingly resembles Reddit.</description><dc:creator>Eli Tan</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 09:01:42 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Meta</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Threads</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Instagram</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Facebook</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mark E Zuckerberg</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">X</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/30/multimedia/META-THREADS-1-03-tgph/META-THREADS-1-03-tgph-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Ian C. Bates for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>“We want to be the largest and best platform for public conversation,” said Connor Hayes, the head of Threads. </med